# Scenario: WRONG APN — Quectel BG96. Customer set APN to "internet" (carrier default
# they remembered from another SIM) instead of "hologram".
# Key signals:
#   +CGDCONT?: APN is "internet" — should be "hologram"
#   +CEREG: 0,1   (registered fine)
#   +CGATT: 1     (data attached fine)
#   +CGACT=1,1 -> ERROR  <-- this is where it breaks
#   +CEER reports cause 33 ("requested service option not subscribed")
# Diagnosis: this is a textbook "everything looks fine until PDP context activation"
# pattern. The carrier is willing to attach the SIM but refuses to bring up a PDP
# context for an APN this SIM is not provisioned to use.
# Customer guidance:
#   AT+CGDCONT=1,"IP","hologram"     # exact string, lowercase, no quotes inside
#   AT+CFUN=0
#   AT+CFUN=1                        # bounce the radio so the new APN takes effect
# If the device firmware re-writes APN on boot, the fix needs to happen in the OEM
# config store, not just the AT shell.
# Reference: cause 33 in 3GPP TS 24.008 Annex G almost always means "wrong APN" or
# "APN not allowed for this subscription."

AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CFUN=1
OK
AT+CGDCONT?
+CGDCONT: 1,"IP","internet","",0,0,0,0
OK
AT+COPS?
+COPS: 0,0,"AT&T",8
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,1
OK
AT+CGATT?
+CGATT: 1
OK
AT+CGACT=1,1
ERROR
AT+CEER
+CEER: "No PDP context activated","SM","Cause: 33 - requested service option not subscribed"
OK
AT+QCSQ
+QCSQ: "CAT-M1",-82,-95,138,-10
OK
